DIAGNOSIS. Large (
32–37 mm
) scorpions. Color is dark, reddish brown, lighter on legs (see 
Figs. 1–2
), telson reddish. Pedipalp movable finger usually with 7 ID denticles and fixed finger usually with 6. Carapace of female is the same size or longer than the metasomal segment V. Mean pectinal tooth count: females 8.916 [n=12], males 11.00 [n=6].
